There are four transport modes in [[Main/en/OpenTTD|OpenTTD]]: Rail, Road, Sea and Air. Each has its own construction method.


*[[File:en/Railroad build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Railway construction|Railway Construction]]''' - Build [[Main/en/Railway station|train stations]], connecting [[Main/en/Building tracks|railway track]], and [[Main/en/Signals|signals]] for [[Main/en/Trains|trains]].
*[[File:en/Road build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Roadway construction|Road Construction]]''' - Build either [[Main/en/Loading Bays#Bus Loading Bay|bus stations]] and [[Main/en/Loading Bays#Lorry Loading Bay|truck stations]], and connect them with roads for [[Main/en/Buses|buses]] and [[Main/en/Road vehicles|trucks]].
*[[File:en/Dock build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Waterway construction|Dock Construction]]''' - Build [[Main/en/Water Transport Tiles|docks]], [[Main/en/Waypoints|buoys]], [[Main/en/Water Transport Tiles|canals]] for [[Main/en/Ships|ships]] to follow.
*[[File:en/Airport build button.png]] '''[[Main/en/Airport construction|Airport Construction]]''' - Build [[Main/en/Airports|airports]] and direct [[Main/en/Aircraft|planes]] between them.

